dct_description_sm: This collection of Groundwater geospatial data was originally published along with Technical Report No. 37: Groundwater Resources of Southeastern Wisconsin by the Southeastern Wisconsin Regional Planning Commission and the Wisconsin Geological and Natural History Survey in coorporation with the Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources in June 2002.Data layers in this collection include Contamination Potential, Depth to Bedrock, Depth to Water Table, Estimated Permeability of the Unsaturated Zone, Estimated Soil Percolation, Significant Hydrologic Data Points, Soil Attenuation, and Water Table Elevation.
dct_creator_sm: Wisconsin Geological and Natural History Survey
